    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Breslau, Ring 59.</placeName>
                    <date>28<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. of May 1873.</date>
                    <salute>Sir!</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>the undersigned, a scholar of Haeckel and Gegenbaur is occupied, to write with some friends a popular “history of the progress of natural sciences since the last 50 years.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>This story will contain with biographical notices of the heroes of science the portraits of these great men.</p>
<p>Now I could not reach any original portrait of yours and it was therefore, that I allowed meself, to beg you, that you might delight me with any (photographical) portrait.</p>
<p>The eternalized Professor, Baron of Liebig at Munich did accept the dedication of the work and has supported me with much kindness in writing it.<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>I hope, that you Sir, whose scientifical magnitude cannot be ackknowledged enough will not refuse, to accomplish my entreaty.</p>
<p>I do but regret, that I am not very well-skilled in English language for expressing better my veneration against you.</p>
<p>With greatest respect | I am | yours very affectionate | R. Hennig, apothecary.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Hennig has not been further identified.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2048.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Ernst Haeckel</ref> and Carl Gegenbaur taught anatomy and zoology in Jena. Hennig’s history has not been identified.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2922.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Justus von Liebig</ref> was professor of chemistry in Munich. He had died on 18 April 1873.</note>
        </div>        
            
